+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772766093824,"sessionID":"ses_33ee83923ffemgKp65fQnWacSH","part":{"id":"prt_cc117e065001gPFBozmWeRRKvI","sessionID":"ses_33ee83923ffemgKp65fQnWacSH","messageID":"msg_cc117dea7002s2NM9Bh2zxYkhd","type":"tool","callID":"b2a57028c","tool":"write","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","content":"---\napplyTo: '**'\n---\n\n# Ralph Plan for CLI Time Tracker\n\n## Original Request\nBuild a TypeScript time tracking library in `src/` that supports starting/stopping named timers, recording entries, persisting to a configurable JSON file, querying entries (all or by date range), summarizing total time per task (including running tasks), error handling for empty names or stopping when none running, and Unicode task names. Export public API from `src/index.ts`. Must compile with strict tsconfig, pass ESLint, and use only built-in Node modules.\n\n## Goal\n- Provide a `TimeTracker` class (or similar) with methods: `start(name:string)`, `stop()`, `getEntries(filter?)`, `getSummary()`, and persistence handling.\n- Define entry types in `src/types.ts`.\n- Ensure data saved to a JSON file whose path can be set via constructor option; automatically create directories.\n- Implement querying by optional start/end `Date`.\n- Summary returns `{[taskName:string]: number}` (milliseconds).\n- Throw `Error` for empty task name on start and for stop when no timer active.\n- Unicode/emoji task names must work (no special handling needed beyond string support).\n- Export all public symbols from `src/index.ts`.\n- Include comprehensive tests covering all requirements.\n- All code must pass `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, and `npm test`.\n\n## Approach (Step‑by‑step)\n1. **Create types** – `Entry` interface with `task:string`, `start:Date`, `stop?:Date`.\n2. **Implement TimeTracker** in `src/index.ts`:\n   - Private fields: `currentEntry?: Entry`, `entries: Entry[]`, `filePath:string`.\n   - Constructor accepts optional `{filePath?:string}` which defaults to `./time-tracker-data.json`.\n   - Helper `load()` reads JSON file if exists; creates directories with `fs.mkdirSync(..., {recursive:true})`.\n   - Helper `save()` writes `entries` (including currentEntry if active) to file.\n   - `start(name)` validates name, stops existing timer if any, creates new entry with `start: new Date()`, pushes previous entry to `entries`.\n   - `stop()` validates there is a running entry, sets `stop: new Date()`, pushes to `entries`, clears `currentEntry`.\n   - `getEntries({from?, to?})` returns copy of entries (including running entry with stop undefined) filtered by dates.\n   - `getSummary()` iterates over all entries plus running entry (duration = now - start) and aggregates milliseconds per task.\n3. **Persistency** – on construction, call `load()`; on each state change (`stop`, `start`, maybe after `stop`) call `save()`.\n4. **Export** – default export `TimeTracker`, and also export `Entry` type from `types.ts` via re‑export.\n5. **Tests** – in `tests/timeTracker.test.ts` using Vitest:\n   - Test start/stop flow, error cases, automatic stop of previous timer.\n   - Test persistence by creating tracker with custom temp file, performing actions, creating new tracker pointing to same file and ensuring entries are loaded.\n   - Test getEntries filter.\n   - Test getSummary includes running timer.\n   - Use Unicode names.\n   - Clean up temp files after tests.\n6. **Run lint/build/tests** – fix any TypeScript/ESLint issues (e.g., unused vars, explicit any, etc.).\n\n## Key Files\n- `src/types.ts`\n- `src/index.ts`\n- `tests/timeTracker.test.ts`\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n- **File I/O errors** – wrap reads/writes in try/catch, rethrow as needed; tests will use writable temp directory.\n- **Date handling** – ensure cloning of dates when returning entries to avoid mutation.\n- **Concurrent modifications** – not required for this simple library.\n- **ESLint rules** – follow project config (no‑unused‑vars, etc.).\n- **Unicode** – Node strings handle Unicode out of the box.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- All unit tests pass (`npm test`).\n- `npm run build` succeeds, emitting .d.ts declarations.\n- `npm run lint` reports no errors.\n- Library functions as described.\n\n## Next Steps\nCreate the todo list (already done) and start implementing `src/types.ts`.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772766093814,"end":1772766093823}}}}
